        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="444" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                <head>No. 444.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Pendleton</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-02-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 7, 1888</date>. (Received February
                        25.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 578.</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: This morning I handed to Count Bismarck, the
                    Imperial secretary of state for foreign affairs the copy of the instruction in
                    regard to Samoan affairs, No. 280, which you sent me under date of January 17,
                    1888.</p>
                <p>1 have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geo. H. Pendleton.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
